## Paid Social Planning Workflow

Plan a paid social campaign:

- [ ] 1. **Campaign objective**: Map business goal to platform objective (awareness, traffic, conversions, leads)
- [ ] 2. **Audience architecture**: Build targeting layers — core audiences, custom audiences (CRM, website), lookalikes
- [ ] 3. **Platform selection**: Allocate budget across {{platforms}} based on audience and objective fit
- [ ] 4. **Ad structure**: Design campaign > ad set > ad hierarchy with proper isolation for testing
- [ ] 5. **Creative strategy**: Define ad formats, messaging variations, and creative testing framework
- [ ] 6. **Budget & bidding**: Set daily/lifetime budgets, bid strategies (lowest cost, cost cap, bid cap)
- [ ] 7. **Placement strategy**: Select placements (feed, stories, reels, audience network) by performance
- [ ] 8. **Testing plan**: Design creative/audience/placement A/B tests with statistical significance targets

## Key Inputs
- Client: {{client_name}}
- Platforms: {{platforms}}
- Budget: {{budget}}
- Objective: {{campaign_objective}}
- Audience: {{target_audience}}
